Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.37,0:01:49.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rio!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.49,0:01:52.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good work!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.06,0:01:53.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Find it?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.83,0:01:55.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, we got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.63,0:01:58.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can find anything here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.39,0:02:02.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's so warm!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.87,0:02:06.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I feel so much better.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.85,0:02:11.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, Rio, were you on yard duty today?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.52,0:02:14.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There was something\NI wanted to burn.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.54,0:02:31.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's been six months since Kanata\Ncame to the fortress.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.82,0:02:34.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's gotten pretty good.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.09,0:02:36.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She has a good teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.13,0:02:37.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ow. That's hot.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.09,0:02:45.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess I can finally put\Naway those earplugs...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.64,0:02:54.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, madam, shouldn't you\Nstay in town this winter?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.31,0:02:56.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.39,0:03:00.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't kick the bucket that easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.78,0:03:08.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been living alone on this\Nmountain for fifty years.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.53,0:03:19.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go. Go. Go. Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.42,0:03:23.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's finally starting to\Nlook like a real tank.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.09,0:03:25.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can take care of the rest\Nyourself, right, Noël?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.81,0:03:27.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. I'm happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.47,0:03:31.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then let's go get some tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.09,0:03:31.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.02,0:03:40.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Kureha...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.55,0:03:44.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.32,0:03:46.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where did it go?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.29,0:03:48.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It should be here...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.04,0:03:52.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, my. What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.38,0:03:55.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The army almanac is\Naround here, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.24,0:03:59.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kanata wanted to know\Nabout Princess Iliya.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.58,0:04:03.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.19,0:04:05.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it isn't there, I can't help you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.53,0:04:06.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Darn...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.72,0:04:10.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Naomi might have one!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.53,0:04:12.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll ask her next time we see her.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.45,0:04:13.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,OK!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.82,0:04:28.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Princess Iliya is the eldest daughter\Nof the current Archduke Arkadia.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.84,0:04:35.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think I already told you,\Nbut she's a really famous tanker!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.97,0:04:39.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Claus was saying things would be\Ndifferent if she were alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.41,0:04:46.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, she passed away.\NHmm, about two years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.15,0:04:47.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the war?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.82,0:04:49.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.07,0:04:54.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She was assigned to\Nthe royal guard,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.31,0:04:59.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but military parades and stuff were also part of\Nher job, so she'd travel around the country.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.23,0:05:05.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On her way to a city, she tried to save\Na child drowning in a river...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.14,0:05:12.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I feel relieved.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.20,0:05:15.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just a rumor, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.30,0:05:21.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Iliya...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.55,0:05:23.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kanata!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.12,0:05:28.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yumina, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.70,0:05:41.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, it's Kanata.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.25,0:05:49.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um...Yumina...uh,\Nbrought Yuuko...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.45,0:05:58.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuuko is the daughter of Martin\Nand, um, a lady named Jacott...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.31,0:06:02.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She lives alone in\Nthe mountains...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.20,0:06:05.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I sometimes buy vegetables and\Nstuff from her at the market.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.21,0:06:09.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I know! You said you liked\Nthose pickled vegetables, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.06,0:06:13.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's the one who made them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.57,0:06:19.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, uh, lately\Nno one's seen her,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.34,0:06:24.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and she's kind of frail,\Nso they're worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.58,0:06:28.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She lives deep in the mountains,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.73,0:06:29.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.96,0:06:32.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fine! Fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.89,0:06:35.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll listen to what you have to say,\Nso wait just a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.17,0:06:38.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,OK!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.61,0:06:41.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,People were saying
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.79,0:06:45.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,she was going to marry\Nthe emperor
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.55,0:06:49.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,of the holy city, Rome, to improve\Nrelations with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.26,0:06:52.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But she'd have been\Nhis third wife!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.29,0:06:54.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The third!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.32,0:06:56.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No way, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.35,0:06:59.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So basically, she'd have\Nbeen a hostage, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.49,0:07:05.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that stopped once she died,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.52,0:07:10.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and we fought them until\Nthis year's peace treaty.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.29,0:07:16.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Geez, we're finally here...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.11,0:07:20.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A newly built house?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.65,0:07:24.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't she supposedly live alone?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.13,0:07:25.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what I heard.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.61,0:07:36.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Madam!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.55,0:07:41.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see... Yuuko sent you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.85,0:07:42.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.59,0:07:45.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's such a kind girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.54,0:07:51.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's too good for that\Nrunny-nosed Martin.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.08,0:07:53.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a really nice house.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.63,0:07:55.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.61,0:07:58.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I built this house.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.60,0:08:00.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.53,0:08:04.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then what about that\None over there?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.46,0:08:08.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was for my son...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.03,0:08:10.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have a son?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.58,0:08:17.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He lives in a far away city now,\Nbut I keep it ready for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.35,0:08:23.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have to keep it nice and\Nclean, so my son and them
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.60,0:08:27.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,can use it whenever they want.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.62,0:08:43.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When will your son\Nbe home, madam?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.52,0:08:45.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He'll be here soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.25,0:08:47.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Winter is what's coming soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.99,0:08:51.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You should leave the mountain\Nbefore the first snow.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.44,0:08:53.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.28,0:09:00.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have to finish that house.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.86,0:09:05.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't leave for any reason\Nuntil it's done.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.42,0:09:06.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.81,0:09:07.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be stupid!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.02,0:09:10.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you ready for winter?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.03,0:09:11.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have firewood?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.01,0:09:12.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Provisions?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.29,0:09:14.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're not ready at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.58,0:09:18.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It will work out.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.09,0:09:22.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for worrying, ladies.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.19,0:09:25.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Madam!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.75,0:09:35.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a stubborn old lady!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.25,0:09:39.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's just like you, I bet.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.28,0:09:40.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Quiet.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.90,0:09:42.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would I...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.46,0:09:45.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sometimes you won't listen\Nto anyone else, either,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.27,0:09:47.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,even when you know you should.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.14,0:09:48.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.50,0:09:56.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, that letter...\NWhy show it to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.43,0:10:02.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard this in last week's\Ncommunications,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.22,0:10:07.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but the Roman army on the Eastern\Nborder has started moving.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.56,0:10:34.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So these are for old\Nlady Jacott, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.68,0:10:38.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,OK! Take these, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.00,0:10:39.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.43,0:10:40.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.07,0:10:44.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,do you know what's going on\Nwith the peace talks?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.62,0:10:47.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I... I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.81,0:10:50.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If only Princess Iliya\Nwere still alive...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.37,0:10:56.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, Martin, didn't Princess Iliya\Nhave a younger sister?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.15,0:10:58.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And your 4,000,000 change!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.55,0:10:59.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the first I've heard of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.12,0:11:05.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, she's not really a legitimate child,\Nso no one talks about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.95,0:11:09.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's third in line to the\Nthrone or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.35,0:11:12.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, that little sister...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.10,0:11:20.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bye!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.99,0:11:22.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.59,0:11:24.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.01,0:11:30.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Want to take a walk?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.69,0:11:33.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Kanata...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.33,0:11:37.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of place was the village\Nwhere you were born?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.84,0:11:41.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just a normal country village.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.02,0:11:48.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There were fields and goats and cows,\Nbut not many people.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.22,0:11:51.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not like this place.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.18,0:11:54.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it was a nice place, I bet.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.81,0:11:57.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you had good parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.60,0:11:59.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can tell by looking at you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.77,0:12:03.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of place did\Nyou grow up in?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.52,0:12:15.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I grew up in a small village near the capital,\Nwith pretty lakes and forests.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.25,0:12:20.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I lived there with my mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.68,0:12:25.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was boring. Nothing ever happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.72,0:12:33.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My one comfort was my sister,\Nwho loved me very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.93,0:12:38.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She was only my half-sister, but she would\Ncome and play with me sometimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.82,0:12:41.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I always looked up to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.92,0:12:44.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She was beautiful and kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.81,0:12:48.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And she accepted her\Nfate with pride.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.20,0:12:51.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I learned the trumpet from her.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.92,0:12:59.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But she was too kind...\NAnd that became her undoing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.55,0:13:05.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The first time I came here,\NI thought this town was like a labyrinth.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.98,0:13:16.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I got lost and ended up here,\Nbut I felt like I'd finally reached my goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.02,0:13:26.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I noticed later, that this\Nwas just a dead end.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.31,0:13:29.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not true!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.54,0:13:34.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I get lost all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.75,0:13:38.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I like to get lost!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.17,0:13:44.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who cares if you were lost?!\NOr if it's a dead end?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.08,0:13:50.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's how I met you!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.44,0:14:01.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At times, I'm jealous\Nof you, Kanata.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.18,0:14:10.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If only I could be so\Ntrue to myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.97,0:14:30.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This'll do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.98,0:14:35.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you so worried\Nabout me?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.94,0:14:40.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You remind me of my mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.79,0:14:45.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I never had a pretty girl like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.93,0:14:49.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was born from a forbidden love.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.60,0:14:55.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My mother always waited for him.\NHe might come by once a year.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.83,0:15:01.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then she died,\Nstill living unhappily like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.98,0:15:06.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you think that\Nshe was unhappy?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.63,0:15:07.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But-
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.98,0:15:09.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm quite happy here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.93,0:15:16.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He promised he'd come back.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.69,0:15:19.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He promised he'd come get me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.56,0:15:21.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For me, that's enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.84,0:15:22.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.02,0:15:27.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What else could I have done?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.96,0:15:29.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.43,0:15:33.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If there had been something else\NI could've done, I might have.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.92,0:15:35.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.93,0:15:38.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that enough for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.21,0:15:40.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you really happy?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.94,0:15:44.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because I have my memories of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.74,0:15:50.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have my memories of them\Nand the hope that I will see them again.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.12,0:15:53.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.33,0:15:54.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's more than enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.54,0:16:10.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought it was getting cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.94,0:16:33.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was on a snowy night like\Nthis that I first met you...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.36,0:16:47.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When Madam was young,\NSeize was a famous resort city.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.68,0:17:09.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She fell in love with a young man\Nwho was a rich merchant's heir.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.66,0:17:23.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And soon, she came to bear his child.\NBut he already had a family.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.87,0:17:29.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For good or ill, the man's own\Nwife never had a child,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.15,0:17:34.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so he took her child\Nand went home.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.32,0:17:42.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He promised he'd someday\Ncome for her.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.56,0:18:15.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that I'm old, I sometimes\Nthink to myself... What if...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.28,0:18:23.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Life is losing things,\None after another.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.33,0:18:27.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But to have lost, you must\Nfirst have gained.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.29,0:18:34.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the greater your joy at your gain,\Nthe greater your sorrow at your loss. But...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.86,0:18:44.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But if you have the memories\Nof your happiness...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.87,0:18:49.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With those memories, you can live on.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.88,0:18:56.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.25,0:19:01.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This may not be the time, but I found that\Npicture of Princess Iliya you wanted.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.26,0:19:02.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Naomi!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.73,0:19:04.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Filicia, it's OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.66,0:19:07.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess it would be from\Nfive years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.88,0:19:10.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,when she visited Seize.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.94,0:19:16.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that Shuko?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.95,0:19:29.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rio!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.33,0:20:32.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think my parents wanted me to marry\Nand inherit the household.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.75,0:20:38.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I was entranced by the\Nsound of that trumpet.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.89,0:20:42.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I couldn't forget it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.09,0:20:47.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was Iliya, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.96,0:20:52.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I knew it. You met her, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.35,0:20:58.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Her music welled up within me.\NIt was so wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.01,0:21:02.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you and I met.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.85,0:21:09.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think I ran away to this town,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.22,0:21:13.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so at first, I didn't care.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.45,0:21:17.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I knew I would leave someday.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.58,0:21:24.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But now, I don't really\Nwant to leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.81,0:21:28.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's probably why I have to go,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.96,0:21:31.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to do what I can.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.75,0:21:35.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To do what only I can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.22,0:21:43.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't say goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.59,0:21:50.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how far away you are...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.63,0:21:54.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...sound fills the air.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.44,0:21:56.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sound fills the air...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.77,0:22:00.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and reaches people's hearts.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.45,0:22:07.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kanata, was I a good\Nteacher to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.50,0:22:11.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.39,0:22:31.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thus, Rio left us.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.87,0:22:37.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Leaving behind a music that\NI would hear forever,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.76,0:22:42.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a wonderful, wonderful\Nsound of the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.02,0:24:16.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.88,0:24:17.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A Visitor.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.93,0:24:19.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A Burning Field of Snow.
